This paper is about machine translation, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). The paper specifically focuses on using unsupervised learning techniques to achieve machine translation without parallel data. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which deals with NLP and its computational aspects. 

The paper also heavily relies on deep learning techniques, which suggests that it could also fall under cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a novel approach to unsupervised machine translation, which could be of interest to researchers in the field of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). 

The paper uses latent space mapping and reconstruction techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and neural networks (cs.NE). Therefore, these two sub-categories are also likely candidates.
